#Orcish Squatters (#1085) - PARKED (re-probed 2026-06-11 after the
#opponent-chooser round changed && chain semantics):
#  - The trigger fires on the Blockers-EXIT transition (WEventBlockersChosen)
#    and its StackAbility resolves immediately after - confirmed in trace.
#  - The OLD working steal driving (choice 0 + land click at COMBATDAMAGE) no
#    longer drives: the may leg now goes live via MultiAbility's interactive
#    branch and the fog leg waits as a MayAbility::andAfter continuation -
#    menu timing/indices changed. Needs fresh driving exploration.
#  - The fog-vs-damage ordering question is still open: pre-fix the fog fired
#    AT trigger resolution (before the steal) and damage STILL went through -
#    so 'fog from(this) ueot' may be ineffective at the damage step entirely,
#    independent of chain order. Verify fog leg in isolation first.
#OLD steal sequence (pre-chooser-round, for reference):
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:orcish squatters
[PLAYER2]
inplay:darksteel citadel
[DO]
goto attackers
orcish squatters
next
goto combatdamage
goto combatdamage
choice 0
goto combatdamage
goto combatdamage
darksteel citadel
goto combatdamage
goto combatdamage
goto end
goto end
[ASSERT]
ENDOFTURN
[PLAYER1]
inplay:orcish squatters,darksteel citadel
[PLAYER2]
life:20
[END]
